description: Miriam, a piano student at a British girls' school at the outbreak of World War I, meets an odd young man and is forced to confront some dark truths about life during wartime.
name: Vol. 1

description: It must be a love letter?. Megan is the secretary to her handsome boss, Dan. Lately, he has been receiving a letter every day, which bothers her very much. Overcome with curiosity, she finally asks him about the letters. He has been troubled by a girl thirteen years younger than him who has been coming on to him. Her suggestion is for him to pretend that he has a girlfriend and he forces her to take on that role!
name: Vol. 1

description:
The vicious alien Krael do not take prisoners... and yet, Stalag-X exists; the defeated soldiers of humanity corralled together on a barren world for an unknown purpose.

One POW, Joe Human, remains a mystery to all; the only thing his fellow soldiers know of him is his last traitorous act. He "saved" them, gambling that he could cheat death-given enough time.

But this time, perhaps death would have been the easy way out-especially when Joe is singled out by a twisted Krael scientist who proudly takes the nickname "Mengele."

Is there always hope where there is life? Or has Joe Human just replaced a quick ending with an excruciating existence worthy of Hell's darkest corner?

When Abby's best friend got into an accident, Abby's skills as a doctor weren't enough to save her. Now Abby has promised to live enough for the both of them, working herself half to death to put her absolute all into everything. But then Abby is appointed by a supervisor to organize a conference party together with an amazing surgeon named Greg. "If you're going to work with me, you need to be beautiful," he says. Confused as she is, she decides to go with his plan!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Once childhood friends, sweet Aki and shy Fumi, unexpectedly reunite the year they enter separate all-girls high schools. Fumi has learned that romance can have its thorns but in meeting an upperclassman she discovers that, like a flower hibernating through the winter, love too can grow and bloom again come spring. But has there in fact been a little flower, almost too small to see, at her side all along?? Join Aki and Fumi in the first volume of Takako Shimura's touching coming-of-age series as they discover more about who they are, and who they can become.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #1: Flower Tales
  • Chapter #2: Stand By Me
  • Chapter #3: The Storms of Spring
  • Chapter #4: Upon Waking in the Morning
  • Chapter #5: The Secret Garden
  • Chapter #6: Beautiful is Youth
  • Chapter #7: Wuthering Heights (1)
name: Vol. 1

description: Three of Marvel's best books collide as UNCANNY X-MEN, IRON MAN and NOVA cross over! But what force could bring the Children of the Atom, the Armored Avenger and the Human Rocket together? When Cyclops is kidnapped, Iron Man returns to space to settle a score - but ends up embroiled with the fugitive Uncanny X-Men! And when their paths cross with Sam Alexander, the inexperienced new Nova, cosmic sparks will fly as their adventure takes them halfway across the galaxy! Can the unlikely allies cooperate long enough to rescue Cyclops and shut down the villains' outer-space agenda? You've got to read it to find out, effendi! Collecting UNCANNY X-MEN SPECIAL #1, IRON MAN SPECIAL #1 and NOVA SPECIAL #1.
name: TPB

volume.name: Uncanny X-Men/Iron Man/Nova: No End In Sight

description: John fell in love with the daughter of the house he served, and he and Eve were set to elope. However, he meets not his beloved at their meeting place, but a band of ruffians! Betrayed and scarred on his left eye, he vows revenge and leaves his birthplace. Ten years later, he's gathered money and power in his quest for revenge, and finally he has the chance to see a matured Eve again. But he's unaware that she loves him still....
name: Vol. 1

description:
This special giant-sized one shot featuring images of classic gothic horror icon Vincent Price. This book will include a cover by Vincent Price Presents by famed artist Robert Aragon as well as new images from the classic movies Price made famous. Vincent Price Presents has been featured in Fangoria, Comicmonsters.com & AMC.

This volume collects: Vincent Price: Gallery #1-#4.
name: TPB

description: Welcome to the Jean Grey School of Higher Learning, where Wolverine, Storm and a star-studded faculty educate the next generation of mutants! But with their own lives steeped in deadly enemies and personal crises, how can the X-Men guide and educate - let alone defend - the school? And what mysterious organization waits in the shadows to destroy Wolverine's mutant sanctuary? The mysterious Phoenix Corporation wants Quentin Quire, but why? As Wolverine clings to life, Storm, Idie and the kids make a stand against the Phoenix Corporation - while a fleeing Quentin finds a new ally in Cyclops! And only Evan can save Fantomex from certain death, but does he dare? Wolverine and Storm reach a breaking point as the X-Men take on the Phoenix Corporation - with their very future hanging in the balance! Collecting WOLVERINE & THE X-MEN (2014) #1-6.
name: Volume 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

volume.name: Wolverine and the X-Men: Tomorrow Never Learns

description:
The Texas 5th has an easy job: Eradicate the zombie infestation.

But between their Leader's strange obsession, and the looming threat from the remnants of the Federal government, this proud militia's future is in dire straits.

Town by town, they rebuild civilization, clinging to the hope of finding a cache of hidden ordnance that will tip the balance in their favor...
name: Vol. 1

description:
Homeless

Zain and Timur are introduced as orphans. Like many orphans, they find themselves alone in a struggle for survival. By sheer chance, these brothers are taken in by the Ansaars, an ancient secret order of noble individuals, who have sworn an oath of stewardship over the world's worst criminals.

This is where the story begins. As the prison that Zain and Timur call home falls to a greedy king, unimaginable evils are released into the world. With everything lost once again, Zain and Timur are thrust back into a big world. This time, however, it's different. This time, they have a purpose. This time, they must journey across empires to recapture the evils that were unleashed and live on as The Last Ansaars of Zindan.
name: Homeless

description: Michael Moran has rediscovered the power of Miracleman! But unbeknownst to him, Dr. Emil Gargunza, the man behind Project Zarathustra, has set in motion plans decades in the making. In The Red King Syndrome, Gargunza's intentions for Miracleman's wife and unborn child set the stage for a confrontation between creator and creation. The origins of Gargunza and Zarathustra will be revealed, and life and death will be decided deep in the jungles of Paraguay. Collecting MIRACLEMAN (2014) #5-10.
name: Book Two

description: In the final chapter of Batman Beyond 2.0, a visit from his alternate self prompts Terry to start picking up the pieces of his shattered life. After all they've been through, is there still hope for the Bat-family?
name: Alternating Currents, Part 4 of 4: Above and Beyond

description: Batman and Robin are unable to stop the all-powerful Mutant. And now the daughter of the man who was once human may now share his fate.
name: The Man Who Quit Being Human Chapter 3 of 4

story_arc_credits.name: The Man Who Quit Being Human

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Man Who Quit Being Human

description: Madefire's hit Motion Book series returns as a bi-weekly on-going title--just in time for Halloween! The heroes find themselves not enjoying the usual trick-or-treating so decide to spice things up...and that's where things go horribly wrong!
